# TerraNeuron Platform Environment Variables

# ============================================================
# OPTIONAL: Cloud LLM Configuration (Terra-Cortex Hybrid AI)
# ============================================================
# Choose ONE of the following options:

# Option 1: Local Ollama (Recommended for Development/Lab)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Make sure Ollama is running on your host machine: ollama serve
# Pull a model: ollama pull llama3.1
OPENAI_API_KEY=ollama
OPENAI_MODEL=llama3.1
OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434/v1

# Option 2: OpenAI Cloud API (Production)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment and set your cloud provider API key
# OPENAI_API_KEY=replace-with-cloud-provider-key
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=  # Leave empty for OpenAI

# Notes:
# - If OPENAI_API_KEY is not set, terra-cortex will run in LOCAL-ONLY mode (Edge AI only)
# - Local Analyzer always runs (fast, free, rule-based)
# - Cloud Advisor only triggers for ANOMALY detections
# - Ollama models: llama3.1, mistral, codellama, etc.
# - OpenAI models: gpt-4o-mini (cost-effective), gpt-4o (more accurate)

# ============================================================
# Database Credentials (Optional Override)
# ============================================================
# The canonical terra-ops database name is terra_ops.
# MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root
# MYSQL_DATABASE=terra_ops
# MYSQL_USER=terra
# MYSQL_PASSWORD=terra2025

# ============================================================
# Redis Configuration (Optional Override)
# ============================================================
# The same value is used by the Redis server and terra-gateway.
REDIS_PASSWORD=terra2025

# ============================================================
# Security Configuration (Required for terra-ops)
# ============================================================
# DEMO_ONLY placeholder for local development. Replace this with a
# random secret before using JWT authentication outside local testing.
JWT_SECRET=DEMO_ONLY_CHANGE_ME_LOCAL_JWT_SECRET_32_CHARS_MIN

# Comma-separated list of browser origins allowed to call the APIs.
# Do not use "*" here.
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:3001

# ============================================================
# Kafka Configuration (Optional Override)
# ============================================================
# KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS=kafka:9092
# Cortex dedupe uses processing time, not the sensor measurement timestamp.
# KAFKA_EVENT_DEDUPE_RETENTION_DAYS=30
# KAFKA_EVENT_DEDUPE_SWEEP_INTERVAL_SECONDS=300
# Grace period before Cortex exits after a critical Kafka task terminates.
# CORTEX_FATAL_TASK_EXIT_DELAY_SECONDS=5

# ============================================================
# Usage Instructions
# ============================================================
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit .env and add your OPENAI_API_KEY if using cloud AI
# 3. Replace JWT_SECRET before running terra-ops outside local demos
# 4. Replace REDIS_PASSWORD outside local demos
# 5. Start services: docker compose up -d
# 6. Check Cloud Advisor status: curl http://localhost:8082/info
